    },
    {
      "id": "e3dd4a9123ac0378bf4169ad7ce9362688dc5fdc",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2011-05-12 00:54:41.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nI am really not happy that we need to introduce such intimate message structure knowledge outside of relevant ptlrpc parts.\n\nI would prefer if it was totally redone to hide the details and so that the debug_req code as is now would work and all the check to be done internally.\n\nSay need_swab() would check magic first. If the magic does not match that means we need to swab the message first and so the body would need to be swabbed too.\nIf the magic does match then we can see into the body flags to see if it needs to be swabbed or not.\n\nI am not sure if we need to retain lustre_XXX_swabbed() flags at all, seemingly need_swab() conveys the same info.\nSomething like need_swab == !swabbed.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
